      "writtenOn": "2020-10-28T19:49:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m a bit concerned about making this a public API like this. The reality is that this describes a colorspace. It just happens that some drawing APIs (like on Windows) expose a different color space for drawing glyphs and everything else.\n\nSo why isn\u0027t the existing colorspace on SkSurfaceProps? Well, it is on SkImageInfo (through SkColorInfo) since one needs to know how to draw out of it. On the other hand SkSurfaces don\u0027t really have a colorspace (the target may be deferred). Under the hood one can try to get at the colorspace by getting the SkCanvas and calling SkCanvas::imageInfo (which may come back without useful information, what is the colorspace of an skp or an nway canvas?). The colorspace information gets pushed through the Make* calls down to the internal SkDevices. I think that\u0027s somewhat seen here where this information needs to get set down on the device. As a result this may be more of a thing that gets passed as a separate colorspace to the Make* calls than living on the SkSurfaceProps.\n\nIn any event, I need to think about this a bit more to see if there is a cleaner way to express this sort of thing.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 63,
        "startChar": 51,
        "endLine": 63,
        "endChar": 93
      },
      "revId": "32005c00ce050c7af386e5e69bebf816eef394c0",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
