      "writtenOn": "2020-10-28T18:12:49Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "My gut says no... since the SK_LUM_COEFF_ macros are used elsewhere in Skia.  The DWrite values have no basis in reality, so it\u0027d be best to use them only for text-mask adjustments.\n\nMy understanding is that the SkMaskGamma code is really only used for the text-mask adjustments... please correct me if I\u0027m wrong.  (That said, the SkColorSpaceLuminance::computeLuminance function is used in one place not directly related to SkMaskGamma---in GrAtlasTextOp.cpp---but it\u0027s at least text related.)",
      "parentUuid": "d99353eb_6c8968c6",
      "revId": "32005c00ce050c7af386e5e69bebf816eef394c0",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
