        "id": 5140
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-10-28T19:49:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "No, the point of SK_LUM_COEFF_X is pretty much to be BT.709. If something like this is really needed we could in theory have a \u0027SK_TEXT_CONTRAST_{RGB}\u0027 or something like that which would default to the BT.709 values but the build could set them otherwise. That being said, I\u0027m not sure where these numbers come from? What is the justification?\n\nNote that in relation to all of this Skia currently doesn\u0027t apply the colorspace from the SkSurface here (and maybe it should). Currently it kinda doesn\u0027t because this glyph colorspace is generally different from the colorspace for everything else. Perhaps just allowing a separate colorspace to be specified fixes that.",
